1. Source & basic app setup
Source: GitHub → repo daverdal/politicalparty, branch master.
Service type: Web service (Node.js).
Build command: npm install
Run command: node src/server.js
HTTP port: 3000
2. Core environment variables (must set)
Replace placeholder values with your real ones.
Auth / security
JWT_SECRET=some-long-random-string-here
OWNER_EMAIL=daverdal@gmail.com
Neo4j (Aura or other)
If using Neo4j Aura:
NEO4J_URI=neo4j+s://YOUR_AURA_ID.databases.neo4j.io
NEO4J_USERNAME=your-aura-username
NEO4J_PASSWORD=your-aura-password
NEO4J_DATABASE=neo4j
If using a self‑hosted Neo4j:
NEO4J_URI=bolt://your-neo4j-host:7687
NEO4J_USERNAME=neo4j
NEO4J_PASSWORD=your-db-password
NEO4J_DATABASE=neo4j
App URL (DigitalOcean URL)
After DO gives you an app URL like https://your-app-name.ondigitalocean.app, set:
APP_BASE_URL=https://your-app-name.ondigitalocean.app
3. Email (Bluehost SMTP)
Use the mailbox you created:
SMTP_HOST=box2024.bluehost.com
SMTP_PORT=465
SMTP_USER=no-reply@manitobasocial.net
SMTP_PASS=the-exact-mailbox-password
SMTP_SECURE=true
EMAIL_FROM="Political Party <no-reply@manitobasocial.net>"
4. Optional / environment
NODE_ENV=production (recommended on DO)
You can copy this list into a note and tomorrow, in DigitalOcean App Platform, just paste each name/value into the Environment Variables section, then deploy.